#Java Modifiers

#Access Modifiers - Controls the access level
#Non Access Modifiers - to provide the other functionality

#Access Modifiers
1.Class - public/default
2. Attributes/variable/method/constructor

	1. public 2.private 3. default 4. protected(Inheritance)
	
#Non Access Modifiers
1.class - final or abstract
final - the class cannot be inherited by other class
abstract - object can't be created

1. attributes and method
static,final,abstract,transient,synchronized

static- we can directly access it using class ..object is not required
final - we can't overriden the method or attributes
abstract - implementation (subclass) - declaration -abstract
transient - when it is required to not serialize the attributes
synchronized - only one thread can access at a time